"a.似是而非的，似乎合理的；嘴巧的 【英】 adj. 似乎合理的(superfic ially reasonable or valuable；嘴巧的(superficiall y pleasing or persuasive) 【记】 plaus(鼓掌)+ible→ 值得鼓掌的→可行的 【同】 派生词:plausibility (n. 似乎有理，善辩) 【例】 The jury believed the witness's plausible testimony. adj. 似乎合理的(看起来或表面上正确的) 【记】plaus鼓掌, ible－值得鼓掌的－似乎合理的 【类】rationalization: plausible = equivocation: definite『obfuscation: indiscernible』合理不是似是而非的 = 模棱两可的话不是明确的『困惑: 难以识别的』 【记】plaus, plaud 鼓掌，喝彩；applause 鼓掌欢迎, 因为看似合理 plausible (adj.)  1540s, ""acceptable, agreeable,"" from Latin plausibilis ""deserving applause, acceptable,"" from plaus-, past participle stem of plaudere ""to applaud"" (see plaudit). Meaning ""having the appearance of truth"" is recorded from 1560s. Related: Plausibly."
